<!doctype html>
<html lang="en">
<head>
  <meta charset="utf-8">
  <meta name="viewport" content="width=device-width, initial-scale=1">
  <title>{{ title }}</title>
  <style>
    body {
      max-width: 720px;
      margin: 4rem auto;
      padding: 0 1.5rem;
      color: #111827;
      font-family: -apple-system, BlinkMacSystemFont, "Segoe UI", sans-serif;
    }

    h1 {
      margin-bottom: 0.5rem;
    }

    p {
      color: #4b5563;
      line-height: 1.5;
    }

    .status {
      border-radius: 0.75rem;
      margin-top: 1.5rem;
      padding: 1rem;
    }

    .status.success {
      background: #ecfdf5;
      color: #065f46;
    }

    .status.error {
      background: #fef2f2;
      color: #991b1b;
    }

    .panel {
      border: 1px solid #e5e7eb;
      border-radius: 1rem;
      margin-top: 2rem;
      padding: 1.5rem;
    }

    .step-label {
      color: #2563eb;
      font-size: 0.9rem;
      font-weight: 700;
      margin: 0 0 0.5rem;
      text-transform: uppercase;
    }

    .step-title {
      font-size: 1.5rem;
      margin: 0 0 0.75rem;
    }

    .expectation {
      background: #f9fafb;
      border-radius: 0.75rem;
      margin-top: 1rem;
      padding: 1rem;
    }

    .expectation strong {
      color: #111827;
    }

    .actions {
      margin-top: 1.5rem;
    }

    button {
      appearance: none;
      border: 0;
      border-radius: 0.75rem;
      background: #2563eb;
      color: #ffffff;
      cursor: pointer;
      display: inline-block;
      font: inherit;
      font-weight: 600;
      padding: 0.85rem 1.1rem;
      text-decoration: none;
    }

    button {
      background: #111827;
    }
  </style>
</head>
<body>
  <main>
    <h1>{{ title }}</h1>
    <p>Follow these steps in order. This page will show one action at a time.</p>

    {% if status_message %}
      <p class="status {{ status_kind }}">{{ status_message }}</p>
    {% endif %}

    <section class="panel">
      {% if not call_started %}
        <p class="step-label">Step 1 of 3</p>
        <h2 class="step-title">Start the Google Meet call</h2>
        <p>Click the button below to open the hardcoded Meet link. Join the meeting in your browser.</p>
        <p class="expectation"><strong>What to expect:</strong> You'll leave this control page and land in Google Meet. After you join, come back to this page to add the bot.</p>
        <form class="actions" method="post" action="/start-call">
          <button type="submit" onclick="window.open('{{ meeting_url }}', '_blank', 'noopener');">Start call</button>
        </form>
      {% elif not bot_id %}
        <p class="step-label">Step 2 of 3</p>
        <h2 class="step-title">Add the bot to the call</h2>
        <p>Click the button below to ask Recall to join the bot to the Meet call.</p>
        <p class="expectation"><strong>What to expect:</strong> The bot may take a few seconds to appear in Google Meet. Once it joins, this page will show the camera step.</p>
        <form class="actions" method="post" action="/add-bot">
          <button type="submit">Add bot</button>
        </form>
      {% elif not camera_enabled %}
        <p class="step-label">Step 3 of 3</p>
        <h2 class="step-title">Enable the bot camera</h2>
        <p>Wait until the bot is visible in the Meet participant list, then click below to turn on its webpage camera.</p>
        <p class="expectation"><strong>What to expect:</strong> The bot should start showing the Meetbot avatar/video feed from <code>/camera</code>.</p>
        <form class="actions" method="post" action="/enable-camera">
          <button type="submit">Enable camera</button>
        </form>
      {% else %}
        <p class="step-label">Done</p>
        <h2 class="step-title">Bot camera is enabled</h2>
        <p>The setup flow is complete. You should now see the bot camera in the Meet call.</p>
        <p class="expectation"><strong>If something looks wrong:</strong> restart the server and run through the wizard again with a fresh bot.</p>
      {% endif %}
    </section>
  </main>
</body>
</html>
